#text=While preparing a dinner of Spaghetti and Meatballs tonight , I realized I needed to go grocery shopping to restock my refrigerator .
#text=It was still early and the store wasn ' t close so I made a trip to the store .
#text=I grabbed a shopping cart because I ' m out of eggs , bread , orange juice , milk etc .
#text=I don ' t like can foods but I like to keep some stocked in my cabinet just in case .
#text=I had to eat bread ends because I was out of whole wheat bread .
#text=The store wasn ' t so crowded considering it would be closing in an hour or so .
#text=I got in the shortest line and of course the register broke down .
#text=I could have gotten out of line but I didn ' t .
#text=When I finally got to the register , it was time for my checker to leave .
#text=I had to wait until an assistant manager signed in the register to ring up my purchases .
#text=The register was out of tape so I was delayed again .
#text=I wished I ' d waited until tomorrow .
#text=There were no baggers to bag my groceries so I did it myself .
#text=My total came to $ 51.34 and I only had $ 20.00 cash on me .
#text=That ' s all I thought I was going to spend .
#text=I gave the clerk a credit card which didn ' t go through and the people behind me started blowing and hissing under their breath .
#text=The employees had locked the door I ' d plan to exit out of .
#text=The manager came over and let me out .
#text=My car was the only car parked in the Customer ' s parking lot .
#text=I wished I ' d stayed at home .
